					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Even SMB1 changes palettes mid-room sometimes. Aside from the obvious case where the Mario / Luigi / Fire state changes, it also loads a new palette for Bowzer, and possibly other cases. Not being able to scroll back and forth is probably a big help here.<br /><br />The other thing that's important in SMB2/3 is how levels are frequently divided up into smaller rooms. Very useful for keeping the enemy combinations contained.</div>

